@node "Intro" "What is it for?"


  Blitz Private Investigator3 - we'll just call it I3 from now on ;)
  is simply a little tool that will read through a tokenized Blitz 
  source code and give you a listing of what libraries were used
  and how many times each command was used. 

  In addition, it will recurse into any INCLUDE or XINCLUDE files
  and will cross reference the commands to the line number within
  each source file.

  What is it for?  It is intended for program optimizing - If you
  find that you have used only one or two commands from a particular
  library, you can shrink your exec's size by finding a way to
  eliminate the command(s) - by using different commands, or better
  yet by learning how to do it using the OS functions.

  FEATURES:

  * Runs from WorkBench
  * Customizes itself to your particular Blitz set-up
  * Source included
  * It can also give you a list of the free library numbers
  * PD!  Do what you like with it.

  REQUIRES:

  ReqTools  (It will crash otherwise!)

  KingCON is also recommended, but not required
@endnode

